# CEOS ARD Server - Cron Job Configuration
# ===========================================
#
# This file contains the cron job schedules for automated maintenance tasks.
# Copy this file and adjust paths/schedules as needed for your environment.
#
# Installation Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file: cp crontab.example crontab.production
# 2. Edit paths to match your server setup
# 3. Ensure GITHUB_SERVICE_TOKEN is set in .env file in project root
# 4. Create logs directory: mkdir -p logs
# 5. Install: crontab crontab.production
# 6. Verify: crontab -l
#
# How it works:
# - The cron job changes directory to the project root (cd /path/to/ceos-ard-server)
# - Each maintenance script explicitly loads .env using load_dotenv() at the top
# - Scripts access GITHUB_SERVICE_TOKEN via settings.GITHUB_SERVICE_TOKEN

# ============================================================================
# 1. Pull Request Status Checker
# ============================================================================
# Checks PR status for all workspaces and auto-archives merged/closed PRs
# Frequency: Daily at midnight (00:00)
# Duration: ~10-30 seconds (depends on number of PRs)
# Requirements: GITHUB_SERVICE_TOKEN must be set in .env file
#
0 0 * * * cd ~/ceos-ard-server && pixi run python scripts/check_pr_status.py >> logs/pr_status_check.log 2>&1

# ============================================================================
# 2. Archived Workspace Cleanup
# ============================================================================
# Permanently deletes archived workspaces after 1 month retention period
# Frequency: Daily at 2:00 AM
# Duration: Depends on number of workspaces to delete
# Warning: This permanently deletes files - ensure backups if needed
#
0 2 * * * cd ~/ceos-ard-server && pixi run python scripts/cleanup_archived_workspaces.py >> logs/workspace_cleanup.log 2>&1

# ============================================================================
# Optional: Log Rotation (Clean up old log files)
# ============================================================================
# Delete log files older than 30 days to save disk space
# Frequency: Weekly on Sunday at 4 AM
#
# 0 4 * * 0 find ~/ceos-ard-server/logs -name "*.log" -type f -mtime +30 -delete

# ============================================================================
# Testing & Debugging
# ============================================================================
# Before deploying to production, test each script manually:
#
#   cd /path/to/ceos-ard-server
#   pixi run python scripts/check_pr_status.py --dry-run
#   pixi run python scripts/cleanup_archived_workspaces.py --dry-run
#
# To check if cron is running:
#   tail -f logs/pr_status_check.log
#   tail -f logs/workspace_cleanup.log
#
# To check cron daemon on Linux:
#   sudo systemctl status cron
#
# To check cron daemon on macOS:
#   sudo launchctl list | grep cron
